TITLE: Implementing Visually Hidden Content with CSS for Screen Reader Access
DESCRIPTION: CSS implementation for creating content that is hidden visually but still accessible to screen readers. This technique (often called .sr-only) ensures screen reader users can access content that doesn't need to be visible on screen.

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
.sr-only {
  clip: rect(0 0 0 0);
  clip-path: inset(50%);
  height: 1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  position: absolute;
  white-space: nowrap;
  width: 1px;
}

<button>
  <span class="sr-only">Save</span>
  <span class="save-icon"></span>
</button>
```

